def: Father; religious superior; -- in the Syriac, Coptic, andEthiopic churches, a title given to the bishops, and by the bishopsto the patriarch.
A groove; a fossa; as, the vallecula, or fossa, which separatesthe hemispheres of the cerebellum.
The scaling off of a bone, a rock, or a mineral, etc.; thestate of being exfoliated.
The coarse-grained brownish yellow wood of a small tree(Pisonia obtusata) of Florida and the West Indies. Also called pigeonwood, beefwood, and corkwood.
To put in jeopardy; to expose to loss or injury; to imperil; tohazard. Sir T. North.A people that jeoparded their lives unto the death. Judg. v. 18.
With careful consideration, or deliberation; circumspectly;warily; not hastily or rashly; slowly; as, a purpose deliberatelyformed.
A hook with a long handle. [Obs.] Tusser.
Pertaining to, derived from, or containing, ethyl; as, ethylicalcohol.
